Descriptive statistics:
Tecnhiques used for organising and summarising the data is called Descriptive statistics 

Tecnhiques are =>  1. Measure of Central Tendency: This has 3 types: 
1. Mean 2. Median 3. Mode

2. Measure of dispersion: 
 1. Variance
 2. Standard Deviation


          
Inferential satistics:  

Collect Data, make inferences using some experiments 
this is called inferential statistics 
Experiments used are: Z test and T test 
The data we collect to make inferences is called => Sample data
The data we make consensus on is called => Population data 

Population data >> sample Data

Example:
We have sample of employees salaries in the industry: {10k,50k,20k,30k,40k}
Descriptive statistics use Mean,Median and Average values 
Where as Inferential Statistics find: 
What is the salary of 1000 employees by using above sample employee salaries
1000 employees is population data 